Problem Statement: Predicting House Prices
Imagine you are a real estate analyst. You want to understand the relationship between the Square Footage of a house and its Sale Price. 
Based on historical data, you want to build a model that can predict the price of a house given its size.
In this scenario, we use Simple Linear Regression to find the best-fitting line that represents the relationship:

$$Price = \beta_0 + \beta_1(Square\ Footage) + \epsilon$$

The Python Implementation, we will use scikit-learn, the standard library for machine learning in Python, to train the model and make a prediction.

