Understanding the Results
The Slope ($166.10$): This suggests that for every additional square foot, the house price increases by approximately $166.10.
The Intercept ($2,191.78$): This is the theoretical value of the house if the square footage was zero (often representing the base land value or a statistical starting point).
The Prediction: For a 2,800 sq ft house, the model uses the linear trend to estimate a value of roughly $465,274.
